{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"c9b03144-8497-4e47-b7f8-e7c7043a64c3","content":"The template is **functional but not fully ready** for NuGet publishing. Here's what's missing:\n\n| Field | Status |\n|---|---|\n| `$schema` | ❌ Missing — add for validation & editor support |\n| `identity` | ✅ |\n| `name` | ✅ |\n| `shortName` | ✅ |\n| `author` | ✅ |\n| `description` | ❌ **Missing** — critical for NuGet discoverability |\n| `groupIdentity` | ❌ Missing — needed so multiple versions coexist properly |\n| `precedence` | ❌ Missing — pairs with `groupIdentity` for versioning |\n| `classifications` | ✅ |\n| `tags` | ✅ |\n\n**Key recommendations:**\n1. **Add `description`** — without it the listing looks incomplete on NuGet.\n2. **Add `groupIdentity`** (e.g., `\"MyCompany.WebApi\"`) and `\"precedence\": 100`.\n3. **Add `$schema`**: `\"https://json.schemastore.org/template\"`.\n\nWant me to apply these fixes?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"77666aa3-867f-4050-a414-9f24a96cbfb6","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"Let me review this template.json against the .NET template engine schema requirements for NuGet publishing.\n\nIssues I can identify:\n\n1. **Missing `$schema`** — Not strictly required, but strongly recommended for validation and editor support.\n2. **Missing `groupIdentity`** — Recommended for NuGet templates so multiple versions of the same template can coexist.\n3. **Missing `precedence`** — Goes with `groupIdentity` for versioning.\n4. **Missing `preferNameDirectory`** — Minor, but commonly set for project templates.\n5. **The `defaultValue` for Framework is `net9.0`** — This is fine, but worth noting.\n\n\n6. **No `description`** — Not strictly required by the template engine, but important for discoverability on NuGet.\n7. **`sourceName` is set to \"MyWebApi\"** — This is valid, though I should verify it matches the actual project name in the template.\n\nLooking at what's actually required versus recommended, the core fields like `identity`, `name`, `shortName`, and `author` are present, but for NuGet publishing specifically, I'm missing `$schema` and `description` which would improve validation and discoverability.","outputTokens":755,"requestId":"A7E5:182BD0:161D156:18B7EF8:6A051FCB"},"id":"47591f0e-77e6-41b5-830a-c0eafdeef683","timestamp":"2026-05-14T01:05:30.661Z","parentId":"56e1e115-7505-469f-8b72-7836ddb58fbb"}
